<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-04-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-04-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="362" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d362">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">894A.001/4–2347: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-04-23">April 23,
                            1947</date>.<lb/>[Received April 23—6:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>880. Minister Peng Hsueh-pei, at regular MOI<note n="27" xml:id="d362fn1">Ministry of Information.</note> press conference on April 23, answered
                        following questions re Taiwan situation: <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“Query: When will Dr. Wei Tao-ming<note n="28" xml:id="d362fn2">Chinese Ambassador in the United States, 1942–46.</note> assume
                                the governorship of Taiwan. Minister Peng’s answer: No date has been
                                chosen yet but Dr. Wei will proceed to his new post in a few
                                days.</p>
                            <p>Query: When will other recommendations of General Pai Chunghsi be
                                carried out. Minister Peng’s answer: General Pai’s other
                                recommendations will be put into execution one by one following the
                                arrival of the new governor in Taiwan.”</p>
                        </quote>
                    </p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>